    <item>
      <title>Urban densification and building performance</title>
      <link>/project/geneva/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Mar 2014 17:03:36 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>/project/geneva/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This project investigated the impact of soft-densification scenarios on built density and urban performance indicators by developing a parametric model based on a 3D cadastre. Two areas were analysed in central and suburban Geneva where current bylaws allow for roof-raising and suburban infilling interventions in order to incease built density and tackle housing shortage. The analysis highlighted the poor daylight access in high-density urban areas, as well as the limited contribution of roof-stacking to the densification processes.








  
  


